:R-HSA-6783984  a           owl:NamedIndividual , obo:GO_0006546 ;
        rdfs:comment        "The simplest amino acid, glycine, is catabolised by several different pathways. The major pathway is via the glycine cleavage system, comprising dimeric P protein (GLDC), T protein (AMT, GCST), dimeric L protein (DLD) and H protein (GCSH) (Kikuchi et al. 2008)." ;
        rdfs:label          "Glycine degradation" ;
        dc:contributor      "Authored: Jassal, Bijay, 2015-06-18" , "Reviewed: D'Eustachio, Peter, 2015-06-26" , "Edited: Jassal, Bijay, 2015-06-18" , "GOC:reactome_curators" ;
        dc:date             "2026-06-29" ;
